item.title: Lua API Version
item.description:
ðŸ”—Current API

The Lua API version used in darktable 5.4.x is 9.6.0.

Previous API versions were

  • darktable-5.2.x - Lua API 9.5.0
  • darktable-5.0.x - Lua API 9.4.0
  • darktable-4.8.x - Lua API 9.3.0
  • darktable-4.6.x - Lua API 9.2.0
  • darktable 4.4.x - Lua API 9.1.0
  • darktable 4.2.x - Lua API 9.0.0
  • darktable 3.8.x - Lua API 8.0.0
  • darktable 3.6.x - Lua API 7.0.0
  • darktable 3.2.x - Lua API 6.0.0
  • darktable 2.4.x - Lua API 5.0.0
  • darktable 2.2.x - Lua API 4.0.0
  • darktable 2.0.x - Lua API 3.0.0
  • darktable 1.6.1 - Lua API 2.0.2
  • darktable 1.6.0 - Lua API 2.0.1

item.title: attributes
item.description:
This section documents various attributes used throughout the documentation.

ðŸ”—write

This object is a variable that can be written to.

ðŸ”—has_tostring

This object has a specific reimplementation of the “tostring” method that allows pretty-printing it.

ðŸ”—implicit_yield

This call will release the Lua lock while executing, thus allowing other Lua callbacks to run.

ðŸ”—parent

This object inherits some methods from another object. You can call the methods from the parent on the child object
